          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "73-TA-181",
                "field_identifier": "NAT",
                "value": 0.99
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Two stacks of 181Ta targets were",
                "irradiated individually, with thicknesses in the",
                "range of 430 to 590 mu-g/cm2. Each stack was composed",
                "of eight 181Ta foils backed with Al foils of 0.92 to",
                "1.07 mg/cm2 thick and prepared by high vacuum",
                "evaporation technique at the China Institute of",
                "Atomic Energy (CIAE), Beijing."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two Si(Au) surface-barrier detectors, at",
                "angles of +-30 degree with respect to the beam",
                "direction, were used to detect the elastically",
                "scattered particles from an Au foil placed upstream",
                "from the target stack."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " One dedicated high-purity germanium (HPGe)",
                "array coupled to a Versa Module Europa (VME)-based",
                "data acquisition system (DAQ), to measure the induced",
                "activity in the target-catcher assembly. There were",
                "eight detector groups in this array, which could",
                "detect the gamma rays independently. Each group",
                "consisted of two HPGe detectors in a face-to-face",
                "geometry, where single gamma-ray measurement and",
                "gamma-gamma coincidence measurement could be made",
                "simultaneously. A thick Pb shield was inserted",
                "between two detector groups to reduce scattered gamma",
                "rays from neighboring targets and background from",
                "natural radio activity."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The offline gamma ray spectroscopy",
                "method."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The errors are minimum of about 5.4% for the",
                "highest beam energies, and increase as one goes down",
                "in energy to a maximum of about 44% at lower energy.",
                "The errors are mainly due to the statistical",
                "uncertainties."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
